18. Nxd6 exd6 19. Bf4 $14) 11. e4 {The most ambitious response. Now Black is
at a crossroad:} N5b6 (11... Nxc3 {secures c4 for the pieces, but makes
White's centre more stable} 12. bxc3 b5 13. Qc2 Qa5 $6 ({More to the point was
} 13... Nb6 14. Bf4 Qd7 {, taking control over the light-squares, but after}
15. Ng5 Bc4 16. Rfd1 $14 {White's chances are still preferable.}) 14. Bg5 f6 ({
