White was clearly better in Martinovic, S - Schoen, R Bad Woerishofen 2001}) 12.
Qc2 Bg4 13. Ne2 $1 $146 {A deep positional move. By overprotecting d4, White
properly anticipates e7-e5.} ({Weaker is} 13. Rd1 e5 14. dxe5 Qe7 15. h3 Bxf3
16. Bxf3 Nxe5 17. Bg2 Rad8 $11 {Romanishin,O - Glek,I Bonn 1994}) 13... e5 (
13... Bxf3 14. Bxf3 e5 15. Rd1 exd4 16. Nxd4 Qe7 17. Be3 $14) 14. Nxe5 Nxe5 15.
dxe5 Bxe5 ({Hardly better is} 15... Bxe2 16. Qxe2 Bxe5 17. Be3 $14) 16. Bh6 (
16. a4 $5 {is another attractive idea here.}) 16... Re8 17. Rad1 Qe7 18. b3 $14
{White has the more harmonious position.} *

