20... Qb6 ({After} 20... a5 21. Bxb4 axb4 22. Nc6 Qc7 23. Rc1 Bc3 24. Qd5 Kg7
25. Rd1 $14 {the vulnerability of the c5 pawn and the full control over the
h1-a8 diagonal offers White a slight-but long-lasting positional advantage.})
21. Rb1 Rd8 22. Bxb4 {The strong Nb4 has to be liquidated.} ({In case of} 22.
