23. Qe1 a5 (23... Bxd4 24. Rxb4 Qe6 25. Rxb7 Bb6 26. Qe2 {looks difficult for
Black, even though there are bishops of a different colour. In the long run, the
attack on the f7 pawn might be very dangerous.}) 24. a3 Bxd4 25. exd4 Nd6 26.
axb4 a4 27. Ra1 $14 {The a-passer is strong, but it cannot be supported by
Black's rook. Therefore, the compensation is questionable here.} *

